 Bangladesh erupts with joy over win

 - Prime Minister Khaleda Zia congratulates players 

 Jubilant Bangladesh players during a victory lap following their first-ever Test win at the M. A. Aziz Stadium in Chittagong on Monday. (AFP) 

Chittagong: Celebrations broke out across Bangladesh Monday as the cricket-mad nation beat Zimbabwe to record its maiden Test victory. 

People in offices and shops erupted in joy and crowds gathered around TV sets to witness the historic moment. 

Prime Minister Khaleda Zia congratulated the team, coaches and cricket board officials. ?People were glued to the screens. Then they won and everyone got extremely excited, cheering and jumping around with joy,? a fan said. 

The Prime Minister congratulated all those who had contributed to the victory and urged the team to strive to improve its performance further. In Dhaka, offices ground to a standstill too. (AFP) 

